China's second large-scale neutrino experiment project, the Jiangmen Underground Neutrino Observatory (JUNO), is currently under construction at 700 meters underground. The construction team has completed construction of a platform, which will be used during the installation of an acrylic sphere, a key component of the central detector of JUNO.
花字：
坐标 south China's Guangdong Province
The detector, located in the middle of a 44-meter-deep pool, 
consists of a stainless steel truss with a diameter of 41 meters, 
an acrylic sphere with a diameter of 35.4 meters, 
20,000 tonnes of liquid scintillator, 
20,000 20-inch photomultiplier tubes and 
